{
  "title": "Home IDS 🛡️ Tier 2: Engine System Health & Performance",
  "uid": "ids-system-health",
  "tags": ["ids", "tier2", "health", "performance", "showcase"],
  "timezone": "browser",
  "refresh": "10s",
  "templating": {
    "list": [
      { "name": "PROMETHEUS_DS", "type": "datasource", "query": "prometheus", "label": "Prometheus Source" },
      { "name": "LOKI_DS", "type": "datasource", "query": "loki", "label": "Loki Source" }
    ]
  },
  "panels": [
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "Navigation Matrix",
      "gridPos": { "h": 2, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "### 🧭 [Triage Hub](/d/ids-master-hub-ultimate) | [📊 DNS & ML Diagnostics](/d/ids-tier2-dns/home-ids-tier-2-dns-ml-diagnostics) | [🔒 Network & Lateral (Zeek NDR)](/d/ids-tier2-ndr/home-ids-tier-2-network-lateral-zeek-ndr) | [🌍 GeoIP & OSINT Intel](/d/ids-tier2-geo/home-ids-tier-2-geoip-osint-intel) | **⚙️ Engine System Health**"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "📖 Analyst Field Guide: Core Processing Latency & DB Backpressure",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 2 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "#### ⏳ Database Lag & Events Ingest Velocity\n* **What this monitors:** Evaluates the synchronization speed between the Pi-hole and Zeek engines.\n* **🟢 Normal State:** Lag stays strictly under 2.0 seconds.\n* **🔴 Problem State:** If the lag climbs in a diagonal line, the SQLite database may be locked, or the script is experiencing compute starvation."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Collector Database Latency Lag (Seconds)",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 2 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [ { "expr": "home_ids_collector_lag_seconds", "legendFormat": "Database Processing Lag" } ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "unit": "s", "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "value": 0, "color": "green" }, { "value": 5, "color": "orange" }, { "value": 15, "color": "red" } ] }, "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10 } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "SQLite Transaction Event Processing Ingest Velocity",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 2 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [ { "expr": "rate(home_ids_events_processed_total[5m])", "legendFormat": "DNS Events Ingested / Sec" } ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "lineInterpolation": "smooth" } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "📖 Analyst Field Guide: IPS Action Integrity",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 7 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "#### 🛡️ Automated Mitigation Operations\n* **What this monitors:** Tracks the actual execution calls when the IDS decides to block a device.\n* **🔴 Problem State:** If IPS Action Errors rise, the script has lost API connectivity to the Pi-hole or Router Webhook, meaning it detects threats but cannot stop them."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Automated IPS Action Velocity (Blocks & Isolations)",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 7 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [
        { "expr": "increase(home_ids_ips_pihole_blocks_total[5m])", "legendFormat": "Pi-hole API Injections" },
        { "expr": "increase(home_ids_ips_router_isolations_total[5m])", "legendFormat": "Router Webhook Drops" }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "custom": { "drawStyle": "bars", "fillOpacity": 30 } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "IPS Action Errors & API Failures",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 7 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [ { "expr": "increase(home_ids_ips_errors_total[5m])", "legendFormat": "Mitigation Faults" } ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "value": 0, "color": "green" }, { "value": 1, "color": "red" } ] }, "custom": { "drawStyle": "bars" } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "title": "📖 Analyst Field Guide: Alert Pipeline Reliability",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 0, "y": 12 },
      "options": {
        "mode": "markdown",
        "content": "#### ✉️ Notification Queue Retries & Drops\n* **What this monitors:** Validates the operational status of our Telegram alert engine.\n* **🔴 Problem State:** If the alert queue rises alongside metric retry ticks, the system is actively backing off due to Telegram API rate-limiting (HTTP 429) or an internet drop."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Notification Thread Delivery Degradation Metrics",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 8, "y": 12 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [
        { "expr": "rate(ids_alert_delivery_retries_total[5m]) * 60", "legendFormat": "Alert Delivery Retries / Min" },
        { "expr": "rate(ids_alert_delivery_dropped_total[5m]) * 60", "legendFormat": "Alert Handshake Drops / Min" }
      ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "custom": { "drawStyle": "bars", "fillOpacity": 30 } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "Notification Internal Buffer Backlog Queue Size",
      "gridPos": { "h": 5, "w": 8, "x": 16, "y": 12 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "${PROMETHEUS_DS}" },
      "targets": [ { "expr": "home_ids_alert_queue_size", "legendFormat": "Buffered Alert Payloads" } ],
      "fieldConfig": { "defaults": { "thresholds": { "mode": "absolute", "steps": [ { "value": 0, "color": "green" }, { "value": 5, "color": "orange" }, { "value": 20, "color": "red" } ] }, "custom": { "drawStyle": "line", "fillOpacity": 10 } } }
    },
    {
      "type": "logs",
      "title": "🪵 Raw System Diagnostics Log Stream (Loki Integration)",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 17 },
      "datasource": "${LOKI_DS}",
      "targets": [ { "expr": "{job=\"home_ids_alerts\", environment=\"production\"} | json | __error__=\"\"" } ],
      "options": { "showLabels": false, "wrapLogMessage": true, "enableLogDetails": true, "prettifyJSON": true }
    }
  ]
}